<h3 class="bold">Video Example(s):</h3>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-featured">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="mv9ywg" data-video-descrip="In Persona 5 and its Updated Re-release, Persona 5 Royal, battle animations feature stylish character portrait cut-ins whenever a party member lands a Critical Hit or successfully exploits an enemy's elemental weakness. Character portraits for the player's currently active party members also appear when using an All-Out Attack, and a celebratory art splash additionally appears should an All-Out Attack end a battle. This video shows the portraits and All-Out Attack art used for &amp;quot;Kasumi&amp;quot;/Sumire Yoshizawa (codename: Violet), a party member exclusive to Royal's post-game story arc." data-video-title="Persona 5 Royal: Violet" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/mv9ywg_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/mv9ywg.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/SuperMovePortraitAttack" data-video-tropename="Super Move Portrait Attack" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="5.00" data-video-rating-count="4" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/Persona,VideoGame/Persona5,VideoGame/Persona5Royal" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link featured-widget-vid">
<div class="featured-widget-vid-iframe">
